[{"id":4329,"date":"2020-06-08T22:20:09","date_gmt":"2020-06-08T22:20:09","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/cbdcrew.org\/?p=4329"},"modified":"2020-06-11T13:48:30","modified_gmt":"2020-06-11T13:48:30","slug":"4329-2","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/cbdcrew.org\/4329-2\/","title":{"rendered":"Trading Pain Meds for Cannabis?"},"content":{"rendered":"<div id=\"537168729252404109-blog\" class=\"blog-body\">\n<div id=\"wsite-content\">\n<div id=\"blog-post-436513516204453133\" class=\"blog-post\">\n<div class=\"blog-header\">\n<h2 class=\"blog-title\"><a class=\"blog-title-link blog-link\" href=\"https:\/\/www.shifa-shop.com\/blog\/a-growing-number-of-people-are-trading-their-pain-meds-for-weed-study-finds\">A Growing Number of People Are Trading Their Pain Meds for Weed, Study Finds<\/a><\/h2>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Nearly half of users in the study said they\u2019d completely stopped taking a pharmaceutical drug because of medical marijuana.\u00a0<\/em><\/p>\n<p>We at CBD Crew are not surprised by these results.<\/p>\n<p>Speaking to medical growers over the past years we have heard many stories like this.<\/p>\n<p>People taking their lives back and getting a new outlook on their futures.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<blockquote><p><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\"><em>As more states in America <a style=\"color: #ffffff;\" href=\"http:\/\/www.governing.com\/gov-data\/safety-justice\/state-marijuana-laws-map-medical-recreational.html\"><u>legalize marijuana<\/u><\/a>, a new <a style=\"color: #ffffff;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.tandfonline.com\/doi\/full\/10.1080\/02791072.2018.1563314\"><u>study<\/u><\/a> shows that many patients are choosing medical cannabis to supplement or even replace pharmaceutical drugs.<\/em><\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"color: #ffffff;\"><em>The study comes from the University of Michigan Institute for Social Research, which surveyed 450 adults who identified as current cannabis users. Among thos